for private practice","Voluntary protection recommended by medical boards","Necessary only after completing training","Mandatory requirement for medical registration","Optional coverage determined by employer preference"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct answer is that professional indemnity insurance (PII) is a \u003Cstrong\u003Emandatory requirement for medical registration\u003C/strong\u003E in Australia. All registered medical practitioners must maintain appropriate PII arrangements as a condition of their registration with the Medical Board of Australia.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOptional coverage determined by employer preference\u003C/strong\u003E - PII is not optional; it is a legal requirement for registration regardless of employer preferences\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERequired only for private practice\u003C/strong\u003E - PII is mandatory for all registered practitioners, whether working in public or private settings\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENecessary only after completing training\u003C/strong\u003E - PII is required from the beginning of medical practice, including during training\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EVoluntary protection recommended by medical boards\u003C/strong\u003E - PII is not voluntary; it is a mandatory requirement enforced by medical boards\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EProfessional indemnity insurance serves to protect both practitioners and patients by providing coverage for claims arising from medical practice. This includes consideration for run-off cover when ceasing practice to maintain protection against future claims relating to past practice.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Professional indemnity insurance is a mandatory requirement for medical registration in Australia.","Professional indemnity insurance protects both practitioners and patients by providing coverage for claims arising from medical practice."],"references":["The Australian Health Practitioner Regulation Agency (AHPRA). Professional indemnity insurance arrangements [online]. 2019 [Cited 2025 Jan 15]. Available at: https://www.ahpra.gov.au/Registration/Registration-Standards/PII.aspx?_gl=1*19dfyql*_ga*MjE0MTMxODY0MC4xNzM2MTI1ODEw*_ga_F1G6LRCHZB*MTczNjg5NjM5MC42LjEuMTczNjkwMDU1My4wLjAuMA..#.","Medical Board of Australia. Good medical practice: a code of conduct for doctors in Australia [online]. 2020 [Cited 2025 Jan 15]. Available at: https://www.medicalboard.gov.au/codes-guidelines-policies/code-of-conduct.aspx."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64917"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18834"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64917","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/64917"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-15T10:58:37+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-15T10:59:29+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11567"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79613"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"18","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/18"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\uddd1\u200d\u2696\ufe0f","name":"Medicolegal","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"6"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71",